BNY Mellon FAQs






How do I acquire copies of the Annual Report?
You can request a free copy of the Corporation's Annual Report on Form 10-K or the quarterly earnings news release on Form 8-K, as filed with the Securities and Exchange Commission
Learn More


How do I contact Wells Fargo Shareowner Services?
Visit the Wells Fargo Shareowner Services website or call +1 800 205 7699.
Learn More


Are there Dividend Automatic Deposits?
You may enroll online for direct deposit of your dividend checks 24 hours a day, seven days a week at www.shareowneronline.com.
Learn More




Can I purchase shares directly from the company?
The Bank of New York Mellon instituted a direct stock purchase and dividend reinvestment plan (DRP), effective on July 2, 2007. To obtain a prospectus and enrollment form, visit the Wells Fargo Shareowner Services website or call +1 800 205 7699.
Learn more


What is the Dividend Payment Schedule?
Subject to approval of the board of directors, dividends are paid on BNY Mellon’s common stock in February, May, August and November.
Learn More


What is the best way to express interest in a position at BNY Mellon?
Submitting a resume and applying online is the fastest and most efficient way to express interest in an opportunity at BNY Mellon. Conduct a Job Search to find out more about our current openings.

















































































 















