Ex-Dividend Reminder: Beneficial Bancorp, Tompkins Financial and Bank of New York Mellon


July 26, 2017, 09:59:17 AM EDT
By DividendChannel.com, BNK Invest









































Shutterstock photo


Looking at the universe of stocks we cover at Dividend Channel , on 7/28/17, Beneficial Bancorp Inc (Symbol: BNCL), Tompkins Financial Corp (Symbol: TMP), and Bank of New York Mellon Corp (Symbol: BK) will all trade ex-dividend for their respective upcoming dividends. Beneficial Bancorp Inc will pay its quarterly dividend of $0.06 on 8/11/17, Tompkins Financial Corp will pay its quarterly dividend of $0.45 on 8/15/17, and Bank of New York Mellon Corp will pay its quarterly dividend of $0.24 on 8/11/17. As a percentage of BNCL's recent stock price of $15.91, this dividend works out to approximately 0.38%, so look for shares of Beneficial Bancorp Inc to trade 0.38% lower - all else being equal - when BNCL shares open for trading on 7/28/17. Similarly, investors should look for TMP to open 0.55% lower in price and for BK to open 0.45% lower, all else being equal.

Below are dividend history charts for BNCL, TMP, and BK, showing historical dividends prior to the most recent ones declared. 

Beneficial Bancorp Inc (Symbol: BNCL) : Tompkins Financial Corp (Symbol: TMP) : Bank of New York Mellon Corp (Symbol: BK) : 

In general, dividends are not always predictable, following the ups and downs of company profits over time. Therefore, a good first due diligence step in forming an expectation of annual yield going forward, is looking at the history above, for a sense of stability over time. This can help in judging whether the most recent dividends from these companies are likely to continue. If they do continue, the current estimated yields on annualized basis would be 1.51% for Beneficial Bancorp Inc, 2.19% for Tompkins Financial Corp, and 1.78% for Bank of New York Mellon Corp. 



In Wednesday trading, Beneficial Bancorp Inc shares are currently off about 0.3%, Tompkins Financial Corp shares are up about 0.2%, and Bank of New York Mellon Corp shares are up about 0.2% on the day. 

Click here to learn which 25 S.A.F.E. dividend stocks should be on your radar screen »



