IT Budget




Bank of New York Mellon Corporation provides financial services to institutions, corporations, and high-net-worth individuals worldwide. The company provides various asset management services to corporations, governments, unions, foundations, endowments, and mutual funds, as well as provides asset servicing products to… MoreBank of New York Mellon Corporation provides financial services to institutions, corporations, and high-net-worth individuals worldwide. The company provides various asset management services to corporations, governments, unions, foundations, endowments, and mutual funds, as well as provides asset servicing products to a collection of institutional clients. The Bank of New York Mellon Corporation was founded in July 2007 following a merger between The Bank of New York Company and Mellon Financial Corporation, which was headquartered in Pittsburgh, PA.

BNY Mellon acquired Cutwater Asset Management in 2015.
IT Priorities:
• Security is a major focus for the company, with ongoing issues around data loss prevention (DLP) and addressing the cost of threat management solutions.  This is expected to remain a focus for some time, and the budget for… MoreIT Priorities:
• Security is a major focus for the company, with ongoing issues around data loss prevention (DLP) and addressing the cost of threat management solutions.  This is expected to remain a focus for some time, and the budget for security initiatives is expected to increase.
• The company is using blockchain to improve resiliency. 
• BNY Mellon is engaged in several initiatives intended to improve UX for the company's software products.


IT Structure

The Bank of New York Mellon Corporation is headquartered in New York, NY.  In addition the Bank employs several IT executives who oversee the IT operations of its subsidiaries including Eagle Investment Systems, ClearTran Client Services and Pershing LLC, which includes Albridge, and is located in Jersey City, NJ. The company maintains several Innovation Centers, with the most recent opening in Pittsburgh. The Northpointe data center located near Pittsburgh has received accolades for observing energy efficiency protocols.

The company has approximately 3,000 IT employees in the US, and approximately 13,000 globally.


IT Historical Information

2013:

• Throughout 2013 the company underwent a large virtualization intiative involving its HP Blade servers being virtualized with a combination of VMware, Citrix and Hyper-V technologies.
• The company upgraded to Windows 7 across its 60,000 users in 2013.
• >5 pb data volume company-wide across 6 to 10 data centers, and expects an annual data growth of 6-10%.
• 25-49% of its servers are to be virtualized by the end of 2013.
• Corporate IT manages 45000 mobile devices, while 3000 are managed elsewhere.
• Corporate IT manages 45000 desktops.
• Standardized on 1-2 product vendors with a limited set of hardware.
• Data center strategy is centered on standardizing on rack-mount x86 systems and virtualized servers.
• Long term plan for running new applications is to add servers and virtualize, but no new facilities are scheduled.
• Less than 30% of IT staff is dedicated to the sustenance of its ERP platform.
• Expects around 10 releases/updates a year with its current ERP solution.
• The Bank of New York Mellon Corporation has the following security safeguards in place: regular policy reviews, inventory of personal employee and customer data, inventory of locations where data is stored, documented incident response process, inventory of third parties, encryption of mobile devices, malware and virus protection software on all devices, incident response processes are documented and a continuous compliance model is in place operating under HIPAA, PCI-DSS, , ISO/IEC 27001/27002, NIST 800-53 compliance standards.
• The company uses an outsourced provider to monitor threats across its networks, security devices and data.

2012:

• The company began the Digital Workplace initiative, which was designed to improve employee experience through a reduction of dowtime, failures, and help desk calls. This was achieved analyzing unstructured internal data through the big data analytics software by Splunk.
• The company also released the Xtreme Computing platform, as another data-related initiative for big data, mobility, and virtualization. This platform is based on the company's private cloud.  

The IT budget is typically finalized in Q3.
 





